The paper discusses secure communication in an intelligent transportation system, which involves exchanging data between vehicles and roadside infrastructure. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of cloudlets for authorization and verification suggests a distributed computing (cs.DC) aspect to the paper. The formal attribute-based model for communication also suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect. Finally, the focus on privacy and anonymity suggests a cybersecurity (cs.CY) aspect to the paper.
